**Some matrix tips.**

**1.** A matrix definitionis `M = {m * n};`

**2.** `m` means Row, `n` means Column.

**In your problem.**

Let&#39;s create a Matrix tool to help us to fix the requirement.

    public class SimpleMatrix {

	  int[][] mat; // 2D array

	  public SimpleMatrix(int[][] mat) {
		  this.mat = mat;
	  }

      // Matrix transpose which is to transfer the elements between rows and cols.
	  public SimpleMatrix transpose() {
		  int rowLen = mat.length;
		  int colLen = mat[0].length;

		  int[][] clones = new int[rowLen][colLen];
		  for (int i = 0; i &lt; rowLen; i++) {
			  for (int j = 0; j &lt; colLen; j++) {
			  	  clones[j][i] = mat[i][j];
			  }
		  }

		  mat = clones;
		  return this;
	  }
	
	  public int[] getRow(int index) {
		  return mat[index];
	  }
	
	  public int sumOfRow(int indexOfRow) {
		  int sum = 0;
		  for (int n : getRow(indexOfRow))
			  sum += n;
		  return sum;
	  }

	  public int[] getColumn(int index) {
		  return transpose().getRow(index);
	  }
	
	  public int sumOfCol(int indexOfCol) {
		  int sum = 0;
		  for (int n : getColumn(indexOfCol))
			  sum += n;
		  return sum;
	  }

In your case, we can declare the 2D nums arary like the var `mat`, and also to get the sum of int[] by using `sumOfRow()`, `sumOfCol()`.

